# Tests CALL - bridging Retron to compiled native code via the same
# loader runmod uses. multifn.o's sum_of_squares(a,b) calls a separate
# square() function twice, then reports the result via host_print - all
# proven working natively; this confirms Retron can drive the same
# mechanism.
# Run: retron call_test.retro (multifn.o must be alongside this script)

CALL "multifn.o" "sum_of_squares" result 3 4
print "sum_of_squares(3,4) via CALL = " & /result
